    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Return to start -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Start Cell Identification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-MAP-2.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall record the maze cell corresponding to the robot&apos;s initial pose as the start cell at the beginning of exploration.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Planning</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      Upon exploration completion, the system shall compute a path from the robot&apos;s current cell to the recorded start cell using the path planning component.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall command the robot to follow the computed path back to the start cell by generating appropriate actuator commands for each segment while still applying collision avoidance.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Second run and efficient path execution -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Initiation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      After the robot has returned to the start cell, the system shall initiate a second run mode that uses the final maze map to traverse from the start cell to the target cell.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Target Cell Definition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall allow configuration of the target cell, such as the maze goal cell or finish area, and shall use this cell as the destination for the second run.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Efficient Path Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-PLAN-3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall use the shortest-path algorithm on the final maze map to compute the most efficient path from the start cell to the target cell for the second run, minimizing at least the total number of cell transitions.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Path Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      During the second run, the system shall command the robot to follow the selected efficient path by issuing time- or distance-parameterized motion commands for each planned movement segment while still enforcing collision avoidance.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RUN-4.3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Completion Detection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-RUN-4.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall detect completion of the second run when the robot enters the target cell and stops all forward motion commands.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Reliability: collision avoidance -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-5.1.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Collision-Free Distance Margin</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall ensure that, under nominal sensor and actuator conditions, the control logic never commands the robot to move such that the estimated minimum distance to any detected wall becomes less than a configured safety margin greater than zero.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-5.1.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Emergency Stop Mechanism</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall implement an emergency stop mechanism that, upon detecting an imminent collision or inconsistent sensor readings indicating possible collision, shall immediately command zero velocity to the actuators.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Reliability: fault tolerance -->

  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-5.2.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Data Validation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-INTERF-6.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall perform validation on each received sensor data packet, including range checks and consistency checks between redundant sensors when available, and shall mark data that fail validation as faulty.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-5.2.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Faulty Data Handling Policy</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      The system shall ignore or down-weight faulty sensor measurements in mapping and collision avoidance computations and shall fall back to last known valid measurements or conservative assumptions when necessary.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-5.2.3">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Degraded Mode Operation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL-EXPL-1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
      When a critical sensor is detected as persistently faulty, the system shall switch to a degraded operation mode that restricts robot speed, reduces exploration aggressiveness, or halts exploration according to a predefined policy.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL-RELIAB-5.2.4">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Fault Logging</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL-RELIAB-5.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
